Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize, says no hospital has reached full capacity but he warns that it's still too early to draw any conclusions from this data. JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize, says hospital admissions are on the decline. He says no hospital has reached full capacity but warns that it's still too early to draw any conclusions from this data. Mhkize says while the COVID-19 numbers are painting a positive picture, it's still important to take precautions. READ: Mkhize tells parents to stick to vaccination schedules He says the wearing of masks, using of sanitisers, and social distancing will help to contain the virus. Meanwhile, the World Health Organization is deploying experts from across the globe to South Africa. Mkhize thanked the WHO for its support. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.